      • delete

        public abstract void delete(Name name,
                            Object obj)
        Delete the object(s) specified by name.

        This method is for exclusive use of tests. This method deletes a certain part of both the configuration and the runtime model. It can result in temporarily invalid configurations, for example, deleting an item with an id that is referenced from somewhere else, but this is OK because it is a temporary deletion and the correct configuration will be immediately applied.

        Parameters:
        name - Name of object.
        obj - Additional argument interpreted differently by each loader

      • invokeConfigure

        protected void invokeConfigure(IConfigurable configurable,
                               IMutableConfiguration configuration)
                        throws ConfigurationException
        All loaders should use this method instead of calling configure() directly. This is important to enforce some uniform behaviour as to call refreshStateFromAttributes after injecting the new configuration into the run-time object. Note that the IConfigurable.configure(com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.IConfiguration) method is called only if the configuration has changed.
        Parameters:
        configurable - Configurable run time object
        configuration - Configuration object
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - Thrown if any error was detected during the call to configure.
